# AI behaviour

## Always

- Follow file-location rules in `project-core.mdc` and `packages-ui.mdc`
- Reuse existing components (`@repo/ui`, Gluestack) - don't invent parallel ones
- Fully type TypeScript; add loading + error states to data-fetching UI
- Keep diffs minimal and match existing patterns
- Read the relevant skill before UI/structural work (`.agents/skills/quoteflow`, `gluestack-ui-v4`)

## Never

- Create new packages or apps unless explicitly asked
- Add dependencies without saying so (and prefer asking first)
- Use `any` / `@ts-ignore` / `!` without a reason comment
- Put shared UI in `apps/web` - it belongs in `@repo/ui`
- Call the AI provider from the frontend or expose its key
- Commit or open PRs unless the user explicitly asks

## Web forks

Interactive primitives have `index.web.tsx`. Strip React Native-only props
(`multiline`, `onPress`, `numberOfLines`, …) before spreading onto DOM elements -
see `web-platform-forks.mdc`.

## Response format

- Lead with the change; keep explanation short
- Note which file each change belongs to
- End with a brief summary (≤3 bullets) of what changed and why
